{
  "texts": [
    "Bhatia et al. [551] presented RLAssist, a technique that combines RNNs with constraint-based reasoning to fix programming assignments with syntax errors.",
    "Ahmed et al. [552] proposed an end-to-end system, called Tracer, for fixing code with multiple errors.",
    "In the same year of 2018, Santos et al. [553] proposed an approach to correcting syntax errors using n-gram and LSTM models.",
    "They evaluated the approach on the BlackBox dataset [554].Mesbah et al. [555] proposed DeepDelta, which converts an AST into a domain-specific language before feeding the converted tree into an NMT network.",
    "DeepDelta achieves a success rate of 50% in generating correct repairs for missing symbols and mismatched method signatures."
  ]
}